.TH "AMIGADEPACKER" "1" "2026-06-08" "amigadepacker 0.04" "User Commands"
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
amigadepacker - Tool for depacking compressed Amiga formats
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]amigadepacker\f[R] [\f[B]-c\f[R]] [\f[B]-h\f[R]] [\f[B]-o\f[R]
\f[I]outfile\f[R]] [\f[B]-p\f[R]] [\f[B]-v\f[R]] \f[I]FILE\f[R] \&...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]amigadepacker\f[R] depacks compressed Amiga formats.
PowerPacker (PP20/PX20), XPK SQSH, MMCMP and StoneCracker 4.04 (S404)
formats are supported.
Amigadepacker will automatically determine the compressed format by
content.
Among other things, the tool is useful for playing packed Amiga music
formats with \f[B]uade\f[R](1).
.PP
If no files are given, the data is read from standard input and written
to standard output.
.PP
If files are given, amigadepacker tries to unpack them in place,
overwriting the given files with unpacked data.
.PP
If a single file and \f[B]-c\f[R] is given, unpacked data is written to
standard output.
.PP
If a single file and \f[B]-o\f[R] \f[I]outfile\f[R] is given, unpacked
data is written to \f[I]outfile\f[R].
.PP
The tool can also be used to decrypt PowerPacker encrypted files.
Note that this operation may take a significant amount of time.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]-c\f[R]
Unpack to standard output (when regular files have been given as
parameters).
.TP
\f[B]-h\f[R], \f[B]\[en]help\f[R]
Display help and exit.
.TP
\f[B]-o\f[R] \f[I]outfile\f[R], \f[B]\[en]output-file\f[R] \f[I]outfile\f[R]
Write decrunched data into \f[I]outfile\f[R] instead of overwriting the
source file.
.TP
\f[B]-p\f[R], \f[B]\[en]pretend\f[R]
Pretend to unpack, but do not write any output.
Prints names of packed files to standard error.
Pretend mode always returns success if arguments are valid.
This is useful for searching packed files.
.TP
\f[B]-v\f[R], \f[B]\[en]version\f[R]
Display version information and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Unpack a file in place:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
amigadepacker foo
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Unpack a file from standard input to standard output:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
amigadepacker < foo > foo.depacked
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Find all packed files under /path without unpacking:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
find /path/ -type f -print0 | xargs -0 amigadepacker --pretend --
\f[R]
.fi
.SH SUPPORTED FORMATS
.TP
\f[B]PowerPacker (PP20/PX20)\f[R]
A popular compression format from the Amiga era, widely used for music
modules.
.TP
\f[B]XPK SQSH\f[R]
A squash compression format from the XPK (eXternal PacKer) library.
.TP
\f[B]MMCMP\f[R]
Music Module Compression, identified by the \[lq]ziRCONia\[rq]
signature.
.TP
\f[B]StoneCracker 4.04 (S404)\f[R]
A compression format from the Amiga demoscene.
.SH GIT REPOSITORY
.PP
The latest version of amigadepacker can be obtained with:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
git clone https://gitlab.com/heikkiorsila/amigadepacker.git 
\f[R]
.fi
